    <body>
      <section eId="sec_139_D">
        <num>139-D</num>
        <heading>Storage and display of firearms, ammunition and explosives</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_139_D__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the establishment and enforcement of standards of design,\nconstruction and maintenance of buildings and structures in which\nfirearms, ammunition or explosives are stored;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_139_D__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the establishment and enforcement of standards of security for the\nstorage of such firearms, ammunition or explosives;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_139_D__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the location of such buildings and structures;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_139_D__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the quantity of firearms, ammunition or explosives which may be\nstored in such buildings and structures;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_139_D__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the manner of such storage; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_139_D__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the times and circumstances under which such firearms, ammunition\nor explosives may be displayed to public view.\n  2. The regulations provided for herein shall not apply to the personal\npossession, use or ownership of firearms or ammunition therefor.\n  3. The exercise of the power granted in this section by a county shall\nrelate only to the area thereof outside any city, or village; the\nexercise of such power by a town shall relate only to the area thereof\noutside the village or villages therein.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
